### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:5000/api

### 
# This mimics the first message sent in a conversation.
# Note: Since we don't provide a chat_id, the server generates one using Date.now()
### 1. New Chat (User First Prompt)
POST {{baseUrl}}/save_chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "role": "user",
    "parts": [
        {
            "text": "Hello! Can you help me with a React project?"
        }
    ]
}

###

### 2. Follow-up Message (User)
# Using the same chat_id to maintain the thread
POST {{baseUrl}}/save_chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "chat_id": 1777490045413,
    "role": "user",
    "parts": [
        {
            "text": "Hello there"
        }
    ]
}

###

### 3. Model Response
# Note: Changed role to "model" to align with Gemini's naming convention
POST {{baseUrl}}/save_chat
Content-Type: application/json

{
    "chat_id": 1777490045413,
    "role": "model",
    "parts": [
        {
            "text": "Of course! What part of React are you working on?"
        }
    ]
}

###

### 3. Get Chat History (Sidebar List)
# This calls your /api/history endpoint to get the first message of every chat.
# Used to populate the sidebar map() we discussed earlier.
GET {{baseUrl}}/history

###

# This tests your logic that reverses the order and slices to the last 10 messages.
GET {{baseUrl}}/history/1777491644040


### Delete a specific chat
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/history/1777490045413

###

### Wipe the entire database history
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/history